text:
Umar entered the Prophet's room and found him lying on a simple mat that had left marks on his side. The Prophet was wearing only a lower garment. When Umar looked at the Prophet's cupboard, he saw very little - just a handful of barley, some mimosa leaves in the corner, and a leather bag hanging on the side.

Seeing this simplicity while knowing that rulers like Caesar and Khosrau lived in luxury, Umar began to cry. When the Prophet asked why he was weeping, Umar explained that he was saddened to see the marks on the Prophet's side from the rough mat and the scarcity in his cupboard, especially when comparing it to how the rulers of Rome and Persia lived among "fruits and springs" despite the Prophet being Allah's chosen messenger.

The Prophet's response was profound. He asked Umar: "O son of Khattab, are you not pleased that they are for us in the Hereafter and for them in the world?" To which Umar replied, "Of course."
